{
  "schemaVersion": 1,
  "version": 1,
  "_comment": [
    "schemaVersion = structure of this file (bump only on breaking layout",
    "changes). version = content revision; the network updater only adopts",
    "a downloaded list whose version is strictly greater than the current",
    "effective one. Bump 'version' every time the data below changes.",
    "",
    "Curated ad / tracker / fingerprint block list for Ebors.",
    "Compiled from the highest-traffic entries in EasyList, EasyPrivacy and",
    "AdGuard Base — roughly the top fraction of rules that catch the bulk of",
    "real-world ad/tracker requests, hand-tuned to avoid the false positives",
    "that break login, payments and captcha flows.",
    "",
    "Previously these lived as Kotlin string literals in BrowserBlocker.kt.",
    "They were moved here so the data is editable without touching code and",
    "so a future build step / network update can replace this file wholesale.",
    "",
    "Loaded by BrowserBlocker.initialize(context) via the AssetManager.",
    "It lives in assets/ rather than a Java resource because Java resources",
    "are dropped from a shrink-enabled release APK; assets always survive.",
    "",
    "Structure:",
    "  adAndTrackerDomains      - object of category -> [domains]; flattened",
    "                             at load time. Each domain matches itself",
    "                             and every subdomain (suffix match).",
    "  essentialAllowList       - object of category -> [hosts] that must",
    "                             never be blocked by the built-in rules",
    "                             (the user's own block list still wins).",
    "  adPathSignals            - path/query substrings that denote ad-tech",
    "                             traffic on any host.",
    "  subResourceOnlyPathSignals - path substrings dropped only for",
    "                             non-document subresources.",
    "",
    "Note: a handful of adAndTrackerDomains entries carry a path component",
    "(e.g. 'yandex.ru/an'). The host suffix matcher only compares the host,",
    "so those are effectively no-ops today — they are preserved verbatim",
    "from the original source to keep this migration behaviour-neutral."
  ],
